          "name": "How much does a roof replacement cost in Charlotte, NC?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "A roof replacement in Charlotte, NC typically costs between $8,000 and $25,000 depending on roof size, material choice, and complexity. Asphalt shingles average $9,000-$14,000 for a standard home, while metal roofing ranges from $14,000-$28,000."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What certifications should a Charlotte roofer have?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "A qualified Charlotte roofer should have: NC General Contractor License (for projects over $30,000), liability insurance, workers' compensation insurance, and manufacturer certifications like GAF Master Elite, CertainTeed SELECT ShingleMaster, or Owens Corning Preferred. BBB A+ accreditation is also recommended."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Does insurance cover roof replacement in Charlotte after a storm?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes, homeowner's insurance typically covers roof damage in Charlotte caused by hail, wind, fallen trees, lightning, and fire. It does not cover normal wear and tear, roofs over 20 years old (may have reduced coverage), or lack of maintenance. Contact your insurance company within 24-48 hours of damage."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How long does a roof replacement take in Charlotte?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Most residential roof replacements in Charlotte take 1-3 days for standard asphalt shingle installations. Complex roofs or metal installations may take 5-7 days. Weather delays can extend the timeline."
